                    <div id="page-content">
                        

<h3 id="toc0"><span><em>Hi, admins.</em></span></h3>
<p>This is all of us on staff. We know that you guys do more for the wiki than anyone can even guess - and that it must be stressful as all hell. We also know that being on staff is a thankless job, and that it must bite even more as an admin.</p>
<p>Well, we want to show you that it isn't entirely thankless. Below, you're going to find a bunch of messages we've compiled from users and lurkers in our fandom/community who wanted to thank you and tell you how much they appreciate everything that you do. We've included messages of our own as well.</p>
<p>From all of us on staff, thank you for being hardworking, resilient, and the best bosses we could ever ask for. We love you guys and we're glad to call you our Administrators, and even more glad to call you our friends.</p>
<div style="text-align: right;">
<h3 id="toc1"><span><em>- your <span style="text-decoration: line-through;">staff</span> friends</em></span></h3>
</div>
<hr />
<blockquote>
<p>I fucking love you all and the work you do behind the scenes to keep the wiki running. 💙</p>
</blockquote>
<div style="text-align: right;">
<p><em>- DrAnnoyingDog</em></p>
</div>
<blockquote>
<p>Thank you for writing so many amazing articles on the wiki. The SCP Foundation couldn't exist without you amazing people.</p>
</blockquote>
<div style="text-align: right;">
<p><em>- SCP-[DATA EXPUNGED]™#53██</em></p>
</div>
<blockquote>
<p>Thank you so much for all your hard work! I couldn't have done what I've done without you, and I'm so grateful that you've chosen to help keep the wiki a shining beacon of light for the rest of the internet.</p>
</blockquote>
<div style="text-align: right;">
<p><em>- UraniumEmpire</em></p>
</div>
<blockquote>
<p>i feel so damn bad about all the shit y'all have to deal with the more i grow older and older. i use to also be pretty damn annoying when i first joined in the site. i am so glad y'all work this hard to keep this website in stable condition. thank you all so damn much.</p>
</blockquote>
<div style="text-align: right;">
<p><em>- pastarasta1</em></p>
</div>
<blockquote>
<p>Hey. As somebody who’s been slinking around site since Series II, I’d like to thank you all for keeping the lights on remaining vigilant. You’re the reason why I’m still here, even if I’m lurking.</p>
</blockquote>
<div style="text-align: right;">
<p><em>- A lurker who's been here forever</em></p>
</div>
<blockquote>
<p>The Wiki is an amazing community, and you guys make it all possible. You volunteer your time, talents, and experience to run this awesome place and don't get anything in return, which is a damn shame considering how much is owed to y'all. Just know lot of people appreciate you guys, even if we don't get the chance to show it. &lt;3</p>
</blockquote>
<div style="text-align: right;">
<p><em>- rounderhouse</em></p>
</div>
<blockquote>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">[+]&nbsp;This&nbsp;one&nbsp;is&nbsp;very&nbsp;long&nbsp;[+]</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">[-]&nbsp;Hide&nbsp;[-]</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>Dear Admins of the SCP wiki,</p>
<p>You do a great job. Seriously, your dedication to this relatively small corner of the internet dedicated to fanfiction of a 4chan creepypasta from 2007 is astounding, and there are few words I can use to even begin describing your handling of this site. While I don't know much or haven't even met on IRC or Discord some of you, I know for a fact that you each deserve so much praise.</p>
<p>Shoutouts to Zyn: Legitimately, forum upkeep wouldn't be a thing without you. Your handling of ideas and drafts along with the founding of the Butterfly Squad can all be summed up to you, and I can't thank you enough.</p>
<p>Shoutouts to Roget: You've written, like, all the skips (OK, only about 5% of the skips, but that's a lot, OK?) and you've consistently remained dedicated with the site enough to have a whole 5 part essay about the site's history. I love that essay, man, and I hope it's updated soon.</p>
<p>Shoutouts to SoullessSingularity: You're skips are some of my favorites (you somehow made Herobrine an interesting concept), and I'm still amazed how you got almost all the 2XX2 slots. On top of that, you consistently work hard on O5 Command on the disciplinary team, which I can't thank you enough for.</p>
<p>Shoutouts to Dr. Mann and The DeadlyMoose: I'll admit that I haven't gone over much to the Wanderer's Library, but your work in basically making something from nothing is very valiant, and I enjoy your work on the top that.</p>
<p>Shoutouts to Quikngruvn: Old people? On the wiki? Madness! In all seriousness, much like Soulless, your dedication to the disciplinary team is always appreciated, and you're one of the oldest team member out there, only beat by Bright. Speaking of Bright&#8230;</p>
<p>Shoutouts to Bright and Clef: Well, the old guard is here. Even as the site has grown so much, you've tagged along for the ride, and that's always a good sign that it's a quality thing to be part of.</p>
<p>Shoutouts to Silberescher: I'll be real with you, the Fifthists are my favorite GoI, and SCP-3005 is my favorite skip. It's also the subject of my highest rated tale, Fifthdation. In essence, I can't thank you enough for making such an enjoyable little eldritch cult.</p>
<p>Shoutouts to Dexanote: So many excellent contests have been run by you, and you also are extremely dedicated to the disciplinary team. Keep it up!</p>
<p>Without you guys, this site would all fall to ashes, and I would never have improved my writing skills, which'll help me in real life. You're all awesome, all of you.</p>
</div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">[-]&nbsp;Hide&nbsp;[-]</a></div>
</div>
</div>
</blockquote>
<div style="text-align: right;">
<p><em>- Elogee FishTruck</em></p>
</div>
<blockquote>
<p>Many, many, MANY thanks to the admins of the SCP Wiki, for maintaining the site, as well as the multitude of other things that they do. They are sincerely appreciated by essentially everyone in the community!</p>
</blockquote>
